  "alt": "Three arrow maps distinguish a confounder, mediator, and collider by their causal positions.",
  "longDescription": "The first map is a fork: prior preparation points to both flashcard-app use and exam score, so prior preparation is a possible confounder. The second map is a chain: assigned app access points to retrieval sessions, which points to exam score, so retrieval sessions are a proposed mediator. The third map is an inverted fork: app use and seeking extra support both point to inclusion in a help-session sample, so sample inclusion is a collider. The maps express causal assumptions to be defended; the arrows are not produced by correlation alone.",
